summary: The customer wants to know the status of their package and complains about the quality of the product they received. The agent asks for the batch number and informs the customer that the package will be collected by the agent and sent for testing. They also mention that the product might have quality issues as it sometimes happens during production. The customer insists on speaking to the manager and wants to know the address of the plant. The agent agrees to provide the address and asks the customer to wait for a few minutes. The call gets cut abruptly without resolving the issue.
speaker_a_summary: Kijie wishes to register a complaint about a product and speak to a concerned agent regarding the issue. The customer service representative creates a ticket for Kijie, and arranges for a new packet to be sent to him by an agent who will collect the old one for testing and investigation. The agent will then solve the problem, or at the very least, provide Kijie with a new packet of product as a goodwill gesture. The call ends with the customer service representative offering to call Kijie back in a minute, as the line was disconnected.
speaker_b_summary: The narrator is having a heated conversation with someone regarding a packet and factory issues. The narrator describes the issues in detail, mentioning missing bar codes, side effects, and improper packaging. They also mention the lack of hygiene and unsafe conditions in the factory, including no hair caps, gloves, or masks. The narrator expresses their frustration and demands answers as to why these issues are occurring. The narrator also mentions a loan and an issue with a girl, but the clarity of the situation is unclear. The conversation becomes agitated and the narrator threatens to take action if the issues are not resolved. Ultimately, the narrator feels that everything has been ruined and they will do their best to remedy the situation.
